	<p class="text">I think many of the things you wrote about have a great deal of merit. There are somethings I think you may want to add though.<br />
<br />
1: Giving me all my abilities in stage 1, then removing them. I hate that s**t. Metroid did this, as does my others. I can except that I have to continue to gain more power to have a feeling of accomplishment, but if my character has all their abilities in the beginning of a game, don't take them away from me. It pisses me off. By that same token, if I am playing a character with nearly infinite resources, why do I start with the s**ttiest load out. Mass Effect 2 does this. I am given the most advanced interstellar ship in the galaxy, and a pistol. You can outfit me with a ship worth a trillion credits, and a pistol a 17 year old punk carries around for 50.<br />
<br />
2: If a developer wants to give me the option to be good or evil in a game, I want control of when I get to do it. These developers regularly let you dictate the personality of your main character, but the "choices" the give you are exceptionally limited. For some reason, the game developers believe that evil=being a dick. The jerk football QB in high school, he was a dick, but probably not evil, unless he was planning to fill your high schools air vents with tear gas. If they claim that I can be a bad ass, let me actually be a bad ass, and not just a jerk. I know they would rather I take the higher ground, but I want my in game punishment for evilness to be a lot more fighting, and a lot less of my character mouthing off. It can be done, Fallout 3 did a great job of it. <br />
<br />
3: Where did my god damned health bar go. I am sure alot of you love Modern Warfare, but I like to know how much more damage I can take until I die, in real life I can do it. Currently I am at 100% life, and I can take exactly 1 bullet before I die. I hate that I can shoot a guy 4 or five times, and as long as he hides behind a crate, (MW2 has them too) he has healed back to full health in 3 to 4 seconds. It takes me more than that to get up from a hard sneeze, much less a barrage of bullets to the face.<br />
<br />
4: This one I think is the most annoying off all game taboos. Boss Attack patterns. I know this one can be fixed. For anyone who has played any game ever, you know what I mean, that was how you beat every game made 20 years ago. If they can't even give the main boss some level of basic AI, at least give me a challenging and complex battle sequence, so that I can't immediately memorize the final bosses fight pattern. I want to fight the final boss who puts my hard earned skills a challenge, not a boss who I have to beat with the lead bubble. <br />
<br />
5: Let me pause a cutscreen. Similar to skipping it, I want the ability to pause during the cutscene. If any of you have had the horrible expirience of finally beating the level you have just died 100 times on, only to realize that your girlfriend or whatever needs to talk to you right now, and you miss your reward cutscene. This is just annoying, sometimes I have s**t to do. I should be able to pause anytime, don't make me play till you say I am ready. I bought the game I should be able to put it down whenever I want.<br />
<br />
You may not agree with all of those, but I hate them.<br />
<br />
p.s. about loading, I can smoke a cigarette in the time it takes to change floors in ME2, no even planets, floors on my own goddamn ship</p>

		
	
	
	
