	<p class="text">@themightydm: You said it yourself, you haven't played the classic RE games. Calling Dead Space and RE5 for survival horror is a stretch as they are closer to action games with horror themes. Real survival horror is about escaping rather than fighting - it's called surviving for a reason. If you have a PS2, check out Capcom's Hunting Ground for the purest example of what I mean. In that game you don't even have a weapon, leaving you to desperatelly run for your life.<br />
<br />
With that said, RE 1-3 actually gave you plenty of ammo. I've never been short at least with usually a reserve of 90 bullets, but then I don't kill everything just because I can. Most of the zombies can just be avoided without them ever harming you. The games require you to think and manage your resources like that so it's a different way of playing compared to your average action/shooter game.</p>

	
	
		
